metadata.name: Moria
metadata.description:
AI dreams of this when asked to think of a Journey inside Moria! In the fictional world of J. R. R. Tolkien, Moria, also named Khazad-dûm, is an ancient subterranean complex in Middle-earth, comprising a vast labyrinthine network of tunnels, chambers, mines, and halls under the Misty Mountains, with doors on both the western and the eastern sides of the mountain range!

If you go alone, it’s just a Journey. You need to share it to turn it into an Adventure!

Collect this piece and turn this Journey into an Adventure!
